12. Use Container Widget with transform property in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The Container widget in Flutter uses the transform property to apply geometric transformations to its child.

It allows you to:

Rotate
Scale
Translate (move)
Skew

This is done using the Matrix4 class.

//main code

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'dart:math';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: ContainerTransformExample(),
    );
  }
}

class ContainerTransformExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Container Transform Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Container(
          height: 120,
          width: 200,
          color: Colors.red,
          transform: Matrix4.rotationZ(pi / 6), // Rotate 30 degrees
          child: Center(
            child: Text(
              "Rotated Box",
              style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 18),
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}